    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hospital de Mataró</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Piperine acts on the oropharyngeal TRPV1, increasing sensory input and the release of
      substance P. These actions may accelerate the oropharyngeal swallow response, improving the
      swallowing of dysphagic patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
